n Zayd reported: One of the daughters of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, sent a messenger calling for him and telling him that her child or son was on the verge of death. The Prophet said to the messenger, \u201cReturn to her and tell her that\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/09\/11\/rahmah-compassion-for-children\/","url_meta":{"origin":389,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Mercy: The Prophet is merciful to his children","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 11, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: Al-Aqra' ibn Habis saw the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, kissing his grandson Al-Hasan. He said, \u201cI have ten children and I do not kiss any of them.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, whoever does not show mercy will not receive mercy.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5997,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4526,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/08\/allah-more-merciful\/","url_meta":{"origin":389,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Rahmah: Allah more merciful than a mother to her child","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 8, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: Some prisoners of war were brought to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and a nursing woman was among them. Whenever she found a child among the prisoners, she would take it to her chest and nurse it. The Prophet said to us, \u201cDo\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7561,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/03\/rahmah-to-children-mercy\/","url_meta":{"origin":389,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Mercy: The Prophet is merciful to children","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: A\u00a0bedouin\u00a0came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cYou kiss the children? We do not kiss them.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cI cannot put mercy into your heart if Allah has removed it from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5998, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2317 Grade: Muttafaqun\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32625,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/03\/allah-mercy-lut-yusuf\/","url_meta":{"origin":389,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Lut: May Allah have mercy on Prophet Lot","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cMay Allah have mercy upon Lot. He had sought refuge in a strong pillar. If I had remained in prison for as long as Joseph, I would have accepted an offer of freedom.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 a